  "customer_summary": {
    "summary": "The UVZ web application currently runs on Angular 18 and Pattern Library 11.3.1. Security support for Angular 18 ends on 21 Nov 2025, after which no free patches are provided. To keep the application secure, compliant and maintainable, it must be upgraded now to Angular 19 together with Pattern Library 12.6.0 and all related dependencies. If the upgrade is not performed, the system will become vulnerable to unpatched security issues and may breach internal security policies, forcing the team to pay for a costly Never‑Ending Support contract.",
    "impact_level": "high",
    "is_bug": false,
    "workaround": "Continue on Angular 18 only by purchasing Never‑Ending Support from the vendor, which incurs additional cost and does not solve the underlying obsolescence.",
    "eta_category": "medium"
  },
  "developer_context": {
    "big_picture": "UVZ is a client‑facing web portal built with Angular (presentation layer) that consumes backend services written in Java 17. End users are internal staff and external partners who perform administrative tasks through the UI. This ticket addresses the need to move the front‑end from Angular 18 to Angular 19 and to update the Pattern Library from 11.3.1 to 12.6.0. The upgrade is required now because Angular 18 loses its free security support on 21 Nov 2025, exposing the portal to unpatched vulnerabilities. Without the upgrade the product would either become insecure or require a paid support contract, both of which are unacceptable for the business.",
    "scope_boundary": "IN: • Upgrade Angular core, CLI and related packages to v19. • Upgrade Pattern Library (bnotk/ds‑ng) to 12.6.0. • Update Node.js, TypeScript, ng‑bootstrap (including the custom patch), ng‑select, ng‑option‑highlight, ag‑grid‑angular and ag‑grid‑community to versions compatible with Angular 19. • Verify that the vertical action bar continues to function (it is deprecated but supported until PL 13.2.0). • Remove any code, modules or styles that belong exclusively to Angular 18 / PL 11.3.1 and are no longer needed. OUT: • Backend Java services, database schema, infrastructure provisioning, CI/CD pipeline scripts unrelated to the front‑end build, and any non‑UI components. • Feature work unrelated to the upgrade (e.g., new UI screens).",
    "classification_assessment": "",
    "classification_confidence": -1,
    "affected_components": [
      "UVZ Front‑end Application (presentation layer)",
